title: For Sale:  Sheila Simon - breakfast 2/12/13 to discuss gun control
postcontent:
Read down a bit guys if you're in Chicago and want to attend 


February 2013 Newsletter 
 Office of Illinois Lt. Governor 
 Sheila Simon 


February 7, 2013 

Dear phil, 

Across the nation, people are talking about guns. Illinois is no exception. The U.S. 7th Circuit Court of Appeals declared unconstitutional our ban on carrying concealed firearms. The court has given lawmakers until June to pass a law on when and where Illinoisans can carry firearms. The Governor used his State of the State address yesterday to say that guns have no place in our schools, shopping malls or sports stadiums. 

Firearms Working Group: Because of the deadline set by the court, I formed a Firearms Working Group, comprised of new members of the General Assembly, to learn about different perspectives and bridge the geographical divide on gun ownership and use in Illinois. Over the next two months, we will meet with stakeholders on all sides of the debate – from hunters to law enforcement to domestic violence prevention advocates – to promote dialogue and work toward consensus on pending legislation. We started our dialogue yesterday with representatives from the Illinois State Rifle Association and Illinois Council Against Handgun Violence. Meet the working group members and send us your thoughts here. 

Legislative Agenda: This session, my office is pursuing three proposals to increase transparency. We’re developing an “income tax receipt” that will show Illinoisans who e-file their tax returns how their tax dollars are spent. We are fine tuning a bill that will make it easier for taxpayers to determine if public servants have financial conflicts of interest. And we’re continuing to push for College Choice Reports, so students can easily compare cost and graduation information for all the degree-granting institutions in this state. 

Military Communities: To strengthen and protect our state’s military installations, I have called on Illinois’ newest Congressional members to join the federal Defense Communities Caucus. The group advocates to ensure our installations remain active and the voices of our troops, their families and our defense communities are heard. In my capacity as chair of the state’s Interagency Military Base Support and Economic Development Committee, I look forward to working with Reps. Cheri Bustos, Bill Enyart, and Brad Schneider whose districts include Illinois’ largest military installations: Rock Island Arsenal, Scott Air Force Base, and Naval Station Great Lakes, respectively. 

If you are free Tuesday, I invite you to join me for breakfast at the Union League Club in Chicago. I will be announcing three game-changing reforms to make college more affordable. If you cannot make the speech but want to get in touch, feel free to call, visit or email with questions, comments or concerns. 

Sincerely, 

Sheila Simon

postcontent:
I have a 33' Komfort camper trailer I traded for but then changed my mind and headed a new direction.  It has a metal roof added on top of the original roof (which was in good shape) but I was going to set it in a permanent location so the rafters and metal roof on the top would eliminate the need to reseal the roof (as on a regular camper)  This camper has a kitchen (the propane refrigerator is missing) but everything else is there.  It has a dining room area that makes into a bed, a couch that makes into a bed, a full bathroom, closets and a rear master bedroom.  Doors in the living room and in the master bedroom.   I removed the built in bed in the bedroom thinking I would add my own bed arrangement.  The only negative issue (besides needing a refrigerator and propane tanks - I got rid of the small propane tanks because they were outdated and I was going to use bigger bottles) is that the previous owner cut a hole in the bedroom side wall to either add a sliding glass door or to add a building to it.  I have the opening sealed with a canvas.  When they made the opening, they disconnected many of the electrical wires, which I have traced and matched up.  This has 110V lighting, gas lights and 12V lighting, so you could use it hooked to power, or remote on 12V (with solar panels) or off the grid and primitive with gas.  If you wanted something to live in, I think with a little TLC this could be pretty nice.  The previous owner had used it to live in for 6 months out of the year.  I am willing to consider a REASONABLE cash offer or a trade for: 
• AR
• AK
• sniper rifle
• Mini 14
• other offers

I know this needs some work and I'm not looking for a premium price, but I am using it for storage and given the current economics, someone else could put this to a much more productive use.  I will get pictures to interested parties.  It is sold "as is" - but I have listed everything I know that might be a pro or a con.  It will be the buyer's responsibility to move it. title: For Sale/Trade:  FI MODEL D Former Colt Pony mini 1911 380
location: Fort Thomas, KY near Cincinnati, Northern Kentucky, Kentucky
postcontent: This is an FI MODEL D, Cal .380, also known as a Colt Pony (Armslist does not have a category for FI [Firearms International]), with TWO (2) magazines, one original, one NOS aftermarket. Made in Washington, DC, these mini 1911 had an interesting history but this web site gives the background better than I can explain: http://www.star-firearms.com/firearms/guns/d/index.shtml. Made by or for Colt, Star, Iver Johnson and FI. Locked breach, adjustable rear sight, all steel consruction. Serial number CPA 023*** (Colt Pony Automatic = CPA). In the middle 1970s, Colt decided to offer a .380 auto, and chose to partner with Star. The gun (to be called the Pony) was to be assembled in the US, presumably by Colt, from a Star DK slide & associated internals, with a U.S. made frame. A fixed lanyard loop was added to increase height of the gun and the adjustable sights are typical of features added to get points for the 1968 Gun Control Act, which placed restrictions on importation of small handguns. Safety cams hammer off sear for extra protection. Mechanical condition is excellent, pictures tell the story. No operational issues, and everything works as it should. I have shot cleaned and lubed it so it's tested and ready.

title: For Sale:  It is going as predicted: Gun bans aren't going to happen
postcontent:
The gougers don't like my message and almost instantly flag it off. For lack of a forum or otherwise to post, this is the only option so I'll repost again. It is not my intention or wish to misuse the listing service, but you need to hear this message. I also urge anyone sympathetic with our grievance to join me in re-posting this message a couple times a day, the more of us that spread the message, the more who will see it and think. I pains me to think some less informed but well intentioned people may get ripped off by buying from these gougers at the worst possible time. Thank God that windows will be a short one.

Listen up:

Folks, there will be NO ban on "assault" rifles and HIGHLY unlikely there will be any magazine bans either. Haven't you noticed even the most hard-core leftist democrats have already taken a step back? They want nothing to do with this. There was a very serious house cleaning in politics when they did this under Clinton and they know better than to every do it again. 
By now you have all heard what is in the ban proposal. It's a long and rediculous list that everyone knows is a joke. No fool would propose such a bill if they didn't fully expect it to be laughed out of congress... the bill is just to appease the pansy liberal voters... in fact, it's practically dead already.
The Illinios magazine ban fell dead in congress without even going to a vote. If a leftist cesspool like Illinois can't even pass it, what do you think is going to happen at the federal level with this current proposal? Federal democrats are already starting to redirect everyone's attention to immigration reform because the gun-grab battle is already lost and they know it. They were trying to run all those news stories about how 90% of all Americans support background checks trying to make you believe it and it didn't work becasue there are 10 of us to every 1 of them. Politicians may be bastards, but they aren't stupid. One thing they know very well is how to stay in office and every single one of them knows a vote for a gun ban will end their career.

The gun culture is suffering a setback right now brought about by the same people who buy up the newest toy every year at Christmas and try to gouge you on Craigslist so your kid can have one. This practice is utterly disgusting and is seriously damaging the sport. 
STOP buying this stuff from them at these outrageous prices. Seriously... 1500 bucks for a Bushmaster? 1.00+ per round for .223?
All they are doing is causing a short-term shortage and the end is near for them, now they are asking 3 grand for a simple AR-15. Don't fall for it! It's over and I hope none of you paid these stupid prices. This ban proposal will mostl likely be officially dead before March and by mid-summer, there will be a surplus of firearms on the market at very reasonable prices. As soon as the ban proposal fails, no one will even want these rifles anymore and you'll be buying them for discounted prices. These jokers who are trying to rip you off know it's over and are getting desperate. The more intelligent ones are already starting to drop their asking price while the rest hang on for dear life knowing they are going to be stuck with a gun they don't even want. HAHAHA ! Cross your fingers and hope they end up losing money when this is over.

So, just relax, calm down and wait a few months... let the hoarders and ripoff artists get stuck with their scheme to rob you. Most of them don't even realize that a Bushmaster is a bottom of the barrel AR platform... they think it's gold plated... they went and bought one at the gun shop thinking they could flip it and double their money.
I assure you, by this time next year, you will be buying 30 round AK and AR mags for 4 bucks again at the gun shows and semi-auto rifles will be plentiful and reasonable priced... IF you can control yourselves. Stop feeding these animals and they will go away... eventually. DO NOT pay double and triple for these weapons, ammunition and magazines. Believe me, I'm tempted to sell my own at these stupid prices but I refuse to participate in this orgy of idiocy. Keep calm and wait them out. Let them eat the ammo they are hoarding when they get hungry... then maybe those of us who are serious and love our sport will be rid of the baseball card traders trying to get rich off of you overnight. 
Let's all stand together and fight this plague in unison.
Peace
